       #!/bin/bash
       # Post-commit hook: Log changes to CHANGELOG.md

       echo "- $(date): Updated configs - $(git log -1 --oneline)" >> CHANGELOG.md

### Usage: Run ./scripts/git-hooks/post-commit after commits.

### Notes:
- This hook is designed to automatically update the CHANGELOG.md file with each commit.
- It is a simple hook that does not require any additional configuration.
- It is a good idea to run this hook after each commit to keep the CHANGELOG.md file up-to-date.
- It is a good idea to run this hook after each commit to keep the CHANGELOG.md file up-to-date.

